Parliament, Tuesday, 8 October 2019 – A joint meeting of the Standing and Select Committees on Appropriations will tomorrow be briefed by the National Treasury on the conditions attached to the Special Appropriation Bill [B10-2019]. The committees will also be briefed by the Financial and Fiscal Commission (FFC) on its submission on the 2020-21 Division of Revenue. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 9 October 2019
	Time: 10 am 
	Venue: Committee Room M46, Marks Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE STANDING AND SELECT COMMITTEES ON APPROPRIATIONS, MR SFISO BUTHELEZI AND MS DIKELEDI MAHLANGU. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact: Name: Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
	E-mail: flombard@parliament.gov.za A joint committee of Parliament receives submissions on constitutional matters and has to review the Constitution at least once a year.Read more